data.enText: great in amount, size, importance, etc.

data.chText: 那项工程耗费了相当多的时间和资金。
data.enText: The project wasted a considerable amount of time and money.

data.chText: 对这栋建筑物的损坏相当严重。
data.enText: Damage to the building was considerable.

tr: large or relatively large in number or amount or extent or degree
example: the economy was a considerable issue in the campaign
went to considerable trouble for us
spent a considerable amount of time on the problem

value.def: Considerable means great in amount or degree.

example.ex: To be without Pearce would be a considerable blow...
example.tran: 失去皮尔斯将是一个巨大的打击。

example.ex: Doing it properly makes considerable demands on our time...
example.tran: 把这事做好要耗费我们相当多的时间。

example.ex: Vets' fees can be considerable, even for routine visits.
example.tran: 即使是常规检查，兽医的收费也会相当高。

example.ex: Children vary considerably in the rate at which they learn these lessons...
example.tran: 孩子们学习这些课文的速度大不相同。

example.ex: Their dinner parties had become considerably less formal.
example.tran: 他们的晚餐会已经远不如以前正式。
